/a> is expected to become the Chief Minister of <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> for the third time. A source in the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh confirmed that a power-sharing agreement between the BJP and Shiv Sena has been finalised, as per a report by Dainik Bhaskar.&nbsp;</p><p>Under this plan, Fadnavis will serve as Chief Minister for two and a half years. After that, <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/eknath-shinde\" target=\"_blank\">Eknath Shinde</a> will take over. Fadnavis would resign during his term to take on the role of BJPs national president.&nbsp;</p><p>If Fadnavis is promoted to the position of BJP national president before the end of his decided 2.5-year term, other leaders like BJP General Secretary Vinod Tawde or former state president Chandrakant Patil could take over as Chief Minister.&nbsp;</p><p>As per reports, it has been confirmed that <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/shiv-sena-eknath-shinde-resigns-from-cm-post-86721\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Shinde will not assume the role before the agreed period ash he resigned from the CM\'s post</a>. This decision was reached after discussions between Prime Minister Narendra Modi, the BJP\'s central leadership, and RSS Chief Mohan Bhagwat.&nbsp;</p><p>Fadnaviss ability to maintain harmony between the BJP and RSS was reportedly a major factor in this decision. On Sunday night, Eknath Shinde was elected as the leader of the Shiv Sena Legislature Party. All 57 MLA-designates unanimously passed a resolution supporting him.&nbsp;</p><p>Other resolutions praised Shindes leadership in securing victory for the party, thanked PM Modi and Home Minister Amit Shah, and expressed gratitude to the people of Maharashtra for their trust in the <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> alliance. &nbsp;</p><p>In the recent Maharashtra Assembly elections, Fadnavis won the Nagpur South-West seat for the fourth consecutive time. He defeated Congress candidate Praful Gudhe in 2014 by 58,942 votes and Ashish Deshmukh in 2019 by 49,344 votes. </p><p>A power-sharing formula has been devised. The plan includes one Chief Minister and two Deputy Chief Ministers. Based on the number of MLAs, ministerial portfolios will be divided. BJP is expected to get 2224 ministers, Shiv Sena (Shinde faction) 1012, and NCP (Ajit Pawar faction) 8-10. </p><p>To avoid Presidents Rule, the new government must be formed before November 26, when the Maharashtra Assembly\'s term ends. The formal announcement of Fadnaviss appointment is expected soon. The swearing-in ceremony is likely to take place this week.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/devendra-fadnavis-to-return-as-maharashtra-cm-for-third-term-86722\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149630\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 26 Nov 2024 06:30:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:219:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/images_1575021420053_devendra_fadnavis.jpeg?bg=1a100e&crop=646.59375%2C363%2C0%2C0&fit=crop&fitToScale=h%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=363&w=768&width=647\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Maharashtra: Eknath Shinde Resigns from CM post\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1647:\"<p><a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/eknath-shinde\" target=\"_blank\">Eknath Shinde</a> stepped down as the Chief Minister of <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> on Tuesday and was subsequently appointed as the caretaker chief minister by Governor CP Radhakrishnan.</p>\n<p>Shinde, accompanied by his deputies Devendra Fadnavis and Ajit Pawar, visited the Raj Bhavan to meet the Governor as the Maharashtra Assembly\'s term concluded today. However, the question of who will assume the role of the next chief minister remains unresolved.<br><br><strong>Also Read:&nbsp;</strong><a class=\"ml-story-headline color-app-black no-decoration\" href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-sees-fewer-young-and-female-legislators-amid-women\'s-reservation-plans-86717\"><strong>Maharashtra Assembly Sees Fewer Young and Female Legislators Amid Women\'s Reservation Plans</strong></a></p>\n<p>The BJP-led ruling <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> coalition secured a resounding victory in the Maharashtra assembly elections, dashing the Congress-led <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maha-vikas-aghadi\" target=\"_blank\">Maha Vikas Aghadi</a>\'s hopes of reclaiming power.</p>\n<p>Despite the decisive win, the formation of the new government has been delayed due to the Shiv Senas demand for Eknath Shinde to remain as Chief Minister.</p>\n<p>The Mahayuti alliance, consisting of the BJP, Shiv Sena, and Ajit Pawar-led NCP, retained control by winning 230 out of 288 assembly seats, leaving the Aghadi with a mere 46 seats.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/shiv-sena-eknath-shinde-resigns-from-cm-post-86721\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149629\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 26 Nov 2024 06:08:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:209:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/eknath_shinde_1726643013928jfif?bg=dddddc&crop=2449%2C1374.877192982456%2C0%2C129.06140350877195&fit=crop&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=1633&w=768&width=2449\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"MNS candidate in Dahisar questions the reliability of EVMs\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2572:\"<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> Navnirman Sena candidate from Dahisar Assembly Constituency Rajesh Yerunkar has questioned the reliability of counting and EVM machines. He has got only two votes from the electoral roll of the locality where he lives. Therefore, he is shocked and he has raised the question whether his family members did not vote for him, mother and wife also did not vote for me. An audio tape made by him in this regard has started circulating widely.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">In the Dahisar Assembly Constituency, a major fight took place between <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/bjp\" target=\"_blank\">BJP</a>\'s incumbent MLA Manisha Chaudhary, <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/shiv-sena\" target=\"_blank\">Shiv Sena</a>\'s (<a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/uddhav-thackeray\" target=\"_blank\">Uddhav Thackeray</a>) candidate Vinod Ghosalkar and <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mns\" target=\"_blank\">MNS</a>\'s Rajesh Yerunkar. Manisha Chaudhary has been elected from this constituency for the third time. She got 58,587 votes. Ghosalkar is in second position and got 54,258 votes. Yerunkar has got 5,456 votes. However, Yerunkar has received only two votes out of a thousand voters at the polling station in the electoral roll of the area where Yerunkar himself lives. Therefore, he has objected and the video of this has been posted on social media.</p><strong></strong><br><strong>Also Read:&nbsp;<a class=\"ml-story-headline color-app-black no-decoration\" href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-sees-fewer-young-and-female-legislators-amid-women\'s-reservation-plans-86717\">Maharashtra Assembly Sees Fewer Young and Female Legislators Amid Women\'s Reservation Plans</a>\n<br></strong><p dir=\"ltr\"><br>In this regard, Yerunkar said that he had objected to this at the counting center itself and submitted the application to the election decision officer. But the authorities did not listen to us and ordered to arrest us. So we got out of there. There are four voters in my house, me, my wife, daughter and mother. Yerunkar has asked if my family didn\'t vote for me.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Yerunkar also raised questions as to how the battery of some devices was discharged, while the battery of some devices was 99 percent full. There was dissatisfaction with Choudhary in some colonies in Dahisar, where the voters did not even allow him to campaign. Yerunkar has also asked how Chowdhury got a majority in that constituency.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/mns-candidate-in-dahisar-questions-the-reliability-of-evms-86719\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149625\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 26 Nov 2024 05:33:33 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:216:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/images_1565364603024_BBPYLtW.jfif?bg=d1d8d2&crop=1122.1875%2C630%2C76.5625%2C0&fit=crop&fitToScale=h%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=630&w=768&width=1200\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"Maharashtra Assembly Sees Fewer Young and Female Legislators Amid Women&#039;s Reservation Plans\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1630:\"<p>In the recently elected 15th <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> Legislative Assembly, the percentage of female legislators elected has decreased by 8% as compared to the last term. Interestingly, there are plans to introduce the Women\'s Reservation Bill, which will reserve one-third of seats in the Lok Sabha and Vidhan Sabhas for women.</p><p>This term, only 22, or 8%, of the total members are female. This is a drop from the previous term, which had 24 female members, the highest recorded to date.</p><p>Furthermore, the assembly is also seeing its oldest age profile ever. Four percent of members are over 70 years old, the highest in the states history. The average age of assembly members has increased from 49 in 2009 to 54 in 2024.</p><p>About 40% of current members are between the ages of 56 and 70. The number of younger members, aged 25 to 40, has dropped. Only 8% of MLAs belong to this group, down from 14% in the last term.</p><p>Educational qualifications among members have also increased. More legislators now hold advanced degrees than in previous years. In 2014, 13% of MLAs had postgraduate qualifications. That percentage has now grown to 17%.&nbsp;</p><p>Similarly, 42% of MLAs are graduates, up from 40% a decade ago. The data also reveals the professional backgrounds of assembly members. About 86% are from business or agricultural backgrounds. The remaining members have careers in politics, social work, medicine, and law.</p><p>This shift in the assembly\'s makeup reflects changes in demographics, education, and professional diversity.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:136:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-sees-fewer-young-and-female-legislators-amid-women\'s-reservation-plans-86717\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149619\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Nov 2024 13:30:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:176:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/news/images_1522317529761_vidhan_bhavan.jpg?bg=7a756b&crop=1368%2C768%2C0%2C0&fit=fill&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=768&w=768&width=1368\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"Mahayuti&#039;s Oath Ceremony Likely Tomorrow; Devendra Fadnavis Likely To Be Maharashtra CM\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2101:\"<p>As per media reports, <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/bjp\" target=\"_blank\">BJP</a> leader <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/devendra-fadnavis\" target=\"_blank\">Devendra Fadnavis</a> is likely to take oath as Chief Minister of <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> with <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/eknath-shinde\" target=\"_blank\">Eknath Shinde</a> expected to take on the role of Deputy CM, alongside NCP leader <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/ajit-pawar\" target=\"_blank\">Ajit Pawar</a>.</p><p>Eknath Shinde is expected to submit his resignation to the governor on Tuesday, November 26, and remain as a caretaker CM until a new CM and cabinet is sworn in, according to a report in TOI.</p><p>The oath-taking ceremony is likely to be held tomorrow, said Deepak Kesarkar, a senior minister from the Eknath Shinde faction of Shiv Sena.</p><p>Sources further stated only the chief minister and those set to be his deputies are likely to take oath tomorrow. No decision has been taken yet on who else will join the cabinet.</p><p>According to reports, Sena might land up with around 12 ministerial berths and be given some key portfolios. The NCP is also said to end up with around 10 ministerial berths.</p><p>Two days after the November 23 results, the alliance partners are having a key meeting with Home Minister Amit Shah in the national capital on Monday for picking the next chief minister.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> swept 235 of the total 288 seats with the BJP emerging as the largest party with 132 seats. As the BJP emerged a senior partner in the NDA, the opposition targeted Shinde saying he might have to work under Fadnavis.</p><p>It is pertinent to note that the chief ministerial post had been a bone of contention for leaders in Maharashtra that had left the BJP in a political crisis in the past. It led to the united Shiv Sena walk out of the NDA alliance after power tussle between Uddhav Thackeray and Mr Fadnavis in 2019.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:131:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/mahayuti\'s-oath-ceremony-likely-tomorrow-devendra-fadnavis-likely-to-be-maharashtra-cm-86716\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149617\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Nov 2024 13:00:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:213:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/mahayuti_1732534989945jpeg?bg=faf0e7&canvas=0.25&crop=1074%2C755%2Cnull%2C0&fit=fill&fitToScale=h%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=755&w=768&width=1074\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"Maharashtra Assembly Elections 2024: Will both Thackeray&#039;s unite after the defeat in the assembly?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3704:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">Opposition parties have had to accept a big defeat in the recently held <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a> Assembly elections. BJP, Shiv Sena (Shinde) and Nationalist Congress Party (Ajit Pawar) have got more than majority seats in the state. The ruling <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> has got as many as 235 seats. &nbsp;Meanwhile, the opposition Mahavikas Aghadi has to settle for only 49 seats. <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/uddhav-thackeray\" target=\"_blank\">Uddhav Thackeray</a>\'s Shiv Sena has got 20 seats, Congress 16 and NCP (Sharad Pawar) 10 seats in Mavia. Meanwhile, Maharashtra Navnirman Sena, which contested 128 seats, could not win a single seat in the state. In both the previous assembly elections, one MLA of this party was elected. This time their sitting MLA has also been defeated.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">In the 2019 assembly elections, the united Shiv Sena led by Uddhav Thackeray had won 56 seats. After the split, only 13 MLAs remained with Uddhav Thackeray. Meanwhile, both Thackerays have suffered a big loss in this election.</p><strong></strong><br><strong>Also Read: <a class=\"ml-story-headline color-app-black no-decoration\" href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-elections-2024-now-fate-looms-over-bmc-elections-86706\">Maharashtra Assembly Elections 2024: Now fate looms over BMC elections</a>\n<br></strong><p dir=\"ltr\"><br>Uddhav Thackeray\'s Shiv Sena, which held the post of Chief Minister two and a half years ago, has 20 MLAs. <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/raj-thackeray\" target=\"_blank\">Raj Thackeray</a> has no representation in the Legislative Assembly. Due to this, both Thackeray\'s parties will have to rebuild. The need for Raj and Uddhav Thackeray to come together for this development is being expressed. The issues of Marathi people, Marathi identity is the basic agenda of both these parties. Well-wishers of both the parties and leaders are of the opinion that they have to come together for the sake of the Marathi people. So now after the defeat in the assembly, everyone is wondering whether these two brothers and their parties will unite. Meanwhile, Shiv Sena (Thackeray) Rajya Sabha MP Sanjay Raut has reacted to this.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>What did Sanjay Raut say?</strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\">While interacting with the media, Sanjay Raut was aas asked if both brothers Raj Thackeray and Uddhav Thackeray will unite to avoid division of Marathi votes. Both of them should come together. This is the wish of his workers and well-wishers. On this, Sanjay Raut said, this is not a question limited to Raj Thackeray or Uddhav Thackeray. Everyone who loves Maharashtra must come together. Even if it is Prakash Ambedkar, they should also unite. Ambedkar is not Marathi? Do they not have to pay anything to Maharashtra? Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar contributed to the fight for United Maharashtra. He also felt that the Marathi people of Maharashtra should remain one. Ambedkar had warned that if the Marathi people do not stay together, Maharashtra and <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mumbai\" target=\"_blank\">Mumbai</a> will become part of the Hamals and Patiwalas and that is exactly what is happening today.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Sanjay Raut said, every political party and leader of that party who loves Maharashtra, small and big workers, should contribute to Maharashtra and Mumbai. Whether that leader is in BJP, Shinde group or Ajit Pawar\'s NCP, they too must contribute to Maharashtra. Seeing this state of Maharashtra, all those who are worried will come together.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:141:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-elections-2024-will-both-thackeray\'s-unite-after-the-defeat-in-the-assembly-86708\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149603\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Nov 2024 07:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:219:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/uddhav_thackeray_1710748911672.jpg?bg=191f3a&crop=653%2C366.59649122807014%2C0%2C0&fit=crop&fitToScale=w%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=420&w=768&width=653\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"Maharashtra Assembly Elections 2024: Now fate looms over BMC elections\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2774:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">After the assembly election, the discussion of the Brihan<a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mumbai\" target=\"_blank\">mumbai</a> Municipal Corporation (<a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/bmc\" target=\"_blank\">BMC</a>) election has started. Due to the resounding success of the Legislative Assembly, it is now being predicted that the <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> will seize the opportunity and hold elections at the earliest.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">The term of corporators of BMC expired on March 7, 2022. Almost two and a half years have passed since the term of the Municipal Corporation. The richest municipal corporation in the country has been running for two and a half years without people\'s representatives. Currently, the BMC is under the administrator\'s rule. Two budgets of this municipal corporation have been presented by the administrators so far.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Works worth crores were approved, mandates were given. The municipal elections were expected to be held in February 2022. But due to major developments in the politics of the state in these two years, the municipal elections were also stalled. But now the assembly elections have been held and the BJP and the Mahayuti seized huge success. Therefore, there is a possibility that the municipal election will be held soon.</p><strong></strong><br><strong>Also Read: <a class=\"ml-story-headline color-app-black no-decoration\" href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/vinod-tawde-serves-defamation-notice-to-congress-leaders-86701\">Vinod Tawde Serves Defamation Notice to Congress Leaders</a>\n<br></strong><p dir=\"ltr\"><br>It was predicted that the election would be held at the earliest as there is a favourable environment for the BJP and the Mahayuti. It is also expected that this election will be held before the month of May. Ahead of the assembly elections, the fate of the municipal elections was uncertain.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>The decision of 227 wards will be important</strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\">The decision regarding the 227 wards significantly impacted the municipal elections. On the eve of Diwali in 2021, the <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maha-vikas-aghadi\" target=\"_blank\">Maha Vikas Aghadi</a> government decided to increase the number of wards in Mumbai from 227 to 236. At the time, the BJP accused Shiv Sena leaders of manipulating the increase in wards to benefit their party. In July 2022, OBC reservation came into effect, leading to the reservation being removed for the second time. However, some BJP representatives continued to strongly demand reverting the number of wards to 227. Ultimately, the High Court ruled to retain the number of wards at 227.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:114:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/maharashtra-assembly-elections-2024-now-fate-looms-over-bmc-elections-86706\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149598\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Nov 2024 06:03:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:241:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/stock/images_1585592406694_WhatsApp_Image_2020_03_24_at_4.15.45_PM.jpg?bg=908c85&crop=960%2C538.9473684210526%2C0%2C0&fit=crop&fitToScale=w%2C1368%2C768&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=640&w=768&width=960\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"Vinod Tawde Serves Defamation Notice to Congress Leaders\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3421:\"<p>In a significant legal development, <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/bharatiya-janata-party\" target=\"_blank\">Bharatiya Janata Party</a> (<a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/bjp\" target=\"_blank\">BJP</a>) national general secretary and former Maharashtra education minister <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/vinod-tawde\" target=\"_blank\">Vinod Tawde</a> has issued a 100-crore defamation notice to <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/congress\" target=\"_blank\">Congress</a> leaders Mallikarjun Kharge, Rahul Gandhi, and Supriya Shrinate. The notice was prompted by social media posts from the Congress leaders accusing Tawde of being involved in voter bribery ahead of the Maharashtra Assembly elections.\n</p><p><strong>Allegations and Controversy</strong></p><p>The controversy originated from an incident on November 19 at a Nallasopara hotel, where it was alleged that Tawde was distributing 5 crore to influence voters. This led to the Tulinj police in the Vasai-Virar area filing cases against Tawde for purportedly violating the election code of conduct. The Congress leaders were quick to take to social media, using the incident to criticize the BJP. Rahul Gandhi questioned the origin of the alleged 5 crore in a post on X (formerly Twitter), suggesting it was misappropriated public money. Mallikarjun Kharge accused the BJP of using \"money and muscle power\" to influence elections in Maharashtra, further asserting that the states voters would reject such practices.</p><p><strong>Tawde\'s Legal Response</strong></p><p>In his defamation notice, Tawde described the accusations as baseless, false, and malicious. He demanded an unconditional apology from the Congress leaders within 24 hours. The apology, he stipulated, must be prominently published in three leading English, Hindi, and Marathi newspapers, as well as on social media. Failing compliance, Tawde warned of legal repercussions, including criminal charges under Section 356 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita (BNS), which could lead to a two-year prison term. Additionally, he announced plans to initiate civil proceedings seeking 100 crore in damages.</p><p>In a statement shared on social media, Tawde dismissed the allegations as politically motivated attempts to tarnish his and the BJPs image. He emphasized that investigations by the Election Commission and the police had found no evidence of the alleged 5 crore. Tawde accused the Congress of resorting to desperate and misleading tactics to gain political mileage. This case exposes the Congress\'s low-level politics. The BJP stands tall, backed by truth and the peoples trust, Tawde remarked in his post.</p><p><strong>The Road Ahead</strong></p><p>The legal notice escalates tensions between the BJP and Congress as Maharashtra heads into a crucial political phase. Tawdes strong rebuttal, coupled with his threat of criminal and civil action, signals a firm stance against allegations of corruption. The Congress leaders, who are yet to respond to the notice, now face mounting pressure to substantiate their claims or retract their statements. The incident has also raised questions about the role of social media in political discourse and the accountability of public figures in making serious accusations. As the story unfolds, both sides are preparing for what could become a high-stakes legal and political battle.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/politics/vinod-tawde-serves-defamation-notice-to-congress-leaders-86701\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Article at Mumbai Live with article id: 149593\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 24 Nov 2024 10:52:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:182:\"https://www.mumbailive.com/images/media/images/images_1537538927738_vinod_tawde.jpg?bg=a29fa3&crop=1368%2C768%2C0%2C0&fit=fill&fm=webp&h=431.1578947368421&height=768&w=768&width=1368\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"\n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n            \n        \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:125:\"Maharashtra Election Results 2024: Mahayuti To Retain Its Power - List Of Winning Candidates For Key Constituencies In Mumbai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14842:\"<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/mahayuti\" target=\"_blank\">Mahayuti</a> alliance, comprising the BJP, Shiv Sena (Eknath Shinde) and NCP (Ajit Pawar), is set to retain its power in Maharashtra after a thumping majority in the state. However,&nbsp;Chief Minister Eknath Shinde and Deputy Chief Ministers Ajit Pawar and Devendra Fadnavis said the parties will discuss the next Chief Minister.</p>\n<p>As soon as it became clearer that the coalition is set for landslide victory, the NDA chief and Prime Minister Narendra Modi thanked the citizens of <a href=\"https://www.mumbailive.com/en/tag/maharashtra\" target=\"_blank\">Maharashtra</a>. Taking it to social media platform X, he&nbsp;shared: \"<span class=\"css-1jxf684 r-bcqeeo r-1ttztb7 r-qvutc0 r-poiln3\">Development wins! \nGood governance wins! &nbsp;United we will soar even higher! &nbsp;Heartfelt gratitude to my sisters and brothers of Maharashtra, especially the youth and women of the state, for a historic mandate to the NDA. This affection and warmth is unparalleled. &nbsp;I assure the people that our Alliance will keep working for Maharashtras progress. Jai Maharashtra!\"</span></p><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">Development wins!<br><br>Good governance wins! <br><br>United we will soar even higher! <br><br>Heartfelt gratitude to my sisters and brothers of Maharashtra, especially the youth and women of the state, for a historic mandate to the NDA. This affection and warmth is unparalleled. <br><br>I assure the</p> Narendra Modi (@narendramodi) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/narendramodi/status/1860280365920977181?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">November 23, 2024</a></blockquote> <p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;Maharashtra Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar on Saturday lauded the \"Ladki Bahin Yojana\" as a transformative initiative, declaring it the driving force behind Mahayuti\'s resounding electoral success in the state.</p><p>He said: \"Ladki Bahin Yojana became our game changer. It defeated each of our adversaries. I have not seen such a victory in my memory. We will not be swayed away by the victory but this has increased our responsibility for sure. We have to behave responsibly now.\"</p><p>Moreover,&nbsp;Chief Minister Eknath Shinde said that people\'s showered the Mahayuti with love after it worked on policies for women, farmers, unemployed and poor. \"They alleged we are buying leaders, they even went to court, but failed,\" he said.<br>\n</p><div class=\"css-175oi2r r-12kyg2d\"><div class=\"css-175oi2r r-k4xj1c r-18u37iz r-1wtj0ep\"><div class=\"css-175oi2r r-1wbh5a2 r-1a11zyx\"><div class=\"css-175oi2r r-1d09ksm r-18u37iz r-1wbh5a2 r-1471scf\"><div class=\"css-146c3p1 r-bcqeeo r-1ttztb7 r-qvutc0 r-37j5jr r-a023e6 r-rjixqe r-16dba41\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"css-1jxf684 r-bcqeeo r-1ttztb7 r-qvutc0 r-poiln3 r-xoduu5 r-1q142lx r-1w6e6rj r-9aw3ui r-3s2u2q r-1loqt21\" href=\"https://x.com/narendramodi/status/1860280365920977181\"></a><strong>Here\'s list of winning candidates in Mumbai:</strong></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table\" width=\"625\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"216\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Constituency</strong></p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"174\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Candidate</strong></p></td><td style=\"width: 19.9491%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"103\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Party</strong></p></td><td style=\"width: 17.4132%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"131\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Margin</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"216\"><p>Andheri East &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"174\"><p>Murji Patel</p></td><td style=\"width: 19.9491%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"103\"><p>Shiv Sena</p></td><td style=\"width: 17.4132%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"131\"><p>25486</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"216\"><p>Andheri West &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"174\"><p>Ameet Satam &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td style=\"width: 19.9491%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"103\"><p>BJP</p></td><td style=\"width: 17.4132%;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"131\"><p>19599</p></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"216\"><p>Anushakti Nagar &nbsp; &nbsp;</p></td><td valign=\"top\"